(28, 'Kenitra', 'Kenitra is a dynamic city located on the Atlantic coast of Morocco, just north of the capital city, Rabat. Known for its strategic location at the confluence of the Sebou River and the Atlantic Ocean, Kenitra serves as an important industrial and commercial hub while also offering a taste of Morocco’s vibrant culture and history.\n\nThe city is characterized by its modern infrastructure and diverse population, making it a melting pot of cultures and traditions. Kenitra’s waterfront area features beautiful parks and promenades, perfect for leisurely strolls while enjoying views of the river and the ocean.\n\nOne of the highlights of Kenitra is the nearby Mehdia Beach, a popular destination for both locals and tourists. The beach offers a range of activities, including swimming, sunbathing, and various water sports. The picturesque shoreline is lined with cafés and restaurants where visitors can enjoy fresh seafood and local dishes.\n\nKenitra is also steeped in history. The Kasbah of Kenitra, with its traditional architecture and charming streets, invites exploration and offers a glimpse into the city’s past. The city has numerous parks and green spaces, providing residents and visitors with tranquil spots to relax and unwind.\n\nCultural enthusiasts will appreciate Kenitra’s vibrant arts scene, with various festivals and events celebrating Moroccan traditions, music, and dance throughout the year. The local market, or souk, is a bustling hub where visitors can shop for handicrafts, textiles, and delicious local produce.\n\nWith its blend of modernity and tradition, stunning coastal scenery, and rich cultural experiences, Kenitra is an attractive destination for travelers seeking to explore the lesser-known gems of Morocco. Whether you’re relaxing on the beach or wandering through the city’s historic sites, Kenitra offers a unique and memorable experience.', NULL, 1, 500000, 100, 0, 4, 'GMT+1', 4),
(29, 'Safi', 'Safi is a captivating coastal city located along the Atlantic Ocean in Morocco, known for its rich history, stunning landscapes, and vibrant culture. Renowned as one of the country’s major fishing ports, Safi offers a unique blend of traditional Moroccan charm and modern amenities.\n\nOne of the city’s most prominent features is its picturesque coastline, where golden beaches meet the azure waters of the Atlantic. Visitors can enjoy a variety of water sports, including surfing and windsurfing, or simply relax on the sandy shores while soaking up the sun.\n\nSafi is also famous for its historical significance. The city boasts impressive landmarks, including the ancient medina, where narrow streets are lined with charming shops and artisan workshops. Here, you can explore the traditional craft of pottery for which Safi is well-known, with beautiful ceramics available for purchase.\n\nThe city’s historic fortress, the Ksar, offers breathtaking views of the ocean and the surrounding landscape. A stroll along the ramparts provides a glimpse into Safi\'s past and the strategic importance it held as a trading port.\n\nCulinary enthusiasts will find Safi to be a delight, with a rich array of seafood dishes that reflect its maritime heritage. Don\'t miss the opportunity to sample local specialties at one of the many seafood restaurants lining the waterfront.\n\nSafi is also home to various cultural festivals throughout the year, celebrating everything from traditional music to art. These events provide a fantastic opportunity to experience the local culture and engage with the friendly residents.\n\nWith its stunning beaches, rich history, and vibrant cultural scene, Safi is an ideal destination for travelers looking to experience the authentic beauty of Morocco. Whether you\'re exploring its historical sites or enjoying the coastal scenery, Safi promises an unforgettable journey.', NULL, 1, 300000, 40, 0, 4.4, 'GMT+1', 7),
